The paper deals with image question answering, which involves computer vision (CV) and natural language processing (NLP) techniques. Therefore, cs.CV and cs.CL are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also proposes a novel approach using stacked attention networks, which involves machine learning and artificial intelligence (AI) techniques, making cs.AI a likely sub-category as well. The paper also presents experimental results and discusses the performance of the proposed approach, indicating that it involves statistical learning (cs.LG) and information retrieval (cs.IR) techniques.
